<HEADLINE>
<P>
JOSEPH A. LIVINGSTON; AUTHOR OF BUSINESS OUTLOOK COLUMN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Joseph A. Livingston, 84, a Pulitzer Prize-winning reporter whose Business 
Outlook column appeared in more than 50 newspapers across the country twice 
each week. Livingston started his column in 1945 and used the Philadelphia 
Inquirer as his base from 1972 until his death. The Inquirer said that 
Livingston also compiled a twice-yearly survey of economists across the country 
and that it was one of the nation's first consensus economic forecasts. He won 
his Pulitzer in 1964 for a series of articles titled "The Power Pull of the 
Dollar." They described how Communist countries, particularly those of Eastern 
Europe, were being pulled toward the West by a variety of economic forces. In 
Pipersville, Pa., on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
