<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: RAMONA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Ramona child molester was granted a new attorney Wednesday. Michael Murphy 
will now represent Ezra Adams during the sentencing phase of his trial. 
</P>
<P>
Adams was found guilty of 86 counts of child molestation in November by 
Superior Court Judge Louis Boyle. Adams waived his right to a jury trial, 
leaving Boyle to decide his guilt or innocence. 
</P>
<P>
Murphy asked Superior Court Judge David M. Gill for two months to review 
transcripts of Adams' trial to prepare for sentencing and a possible motion 
requesting a new trial. 
</P>
<P>
On Dec. 20 at Adam's request, Boyle relieved attorney Roy Gunner from the case. 
</P>
<P>
Adams faces 330 years in state prison for his convictions of molesting an 
11-year-old San Carlos girl and six girls from Ramona. 
</P>
<P>
Boyle found Adams guilty of 86 lewd and lascivious acts, but found him innocent 
of eight other counts and dismissed two other charges. 
</P>
<P>
Adams will be sentenced Feb. 28. 
</P>
