<HEADLINE>
<P>
SERRA DEFENSIVE BACK NAMED TO ALL-SOUTHERN SECTION TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Serra High defensive back Clayton Lopez, who helped the Cavaliers to a 14-0 
season and the Southern Section Division VII title, has been chosen to the CIF 
All-Southern Section football team by the Amateur Athletic Foundation board of 
sportswriters. 
</P>
<P>
Lopez, a 5-foot-11, 178-pound senior, was one of 25 players selected to the 
elite squad, representing all nine Southern Section divisions. Lopez led Serra 
with eight interceptions and was second on the team in tackles. 
</P>
<P>
He was one of only two players on the team from a Division VII school. The 
other was Lompoc running back Napoleon Kaufman, the division MVP. Serra edged 
Lompoc in the championship game, 34-31. 
</P>
<P>
Bishop Montgomery lineman Chris Maumalanga was the only South Bay player named 
to the All-Division I team. The 6-4, 320-pound senior led the Knights with 86 
tackles and nine sacks. 
</P>
<P>
Linebacker Bobby Sylvester of division champion Fontana and tailback Ron Rivers 
of runner-up San Gorgonio were selected Division I Co-Players of the Year. 
</P>
<P>
The South Bay was well-represented on the All-Division II squad with eight 
selections, two each from Bay League teams Palos Verdes, Hawthorne, Leuzinger 
and Rolling Hills. 
</P>
<P>
Named to the offensive unit were running backs Chris Alexander of Hawthorne and 
Robert Coulter of Rolling Hills, lineman Jim Justice and place-kicker Angel 
Andrade of Leuzinger and Palos Verdes quarterback Blake Anderson, chosen as an 
all-purpose player for his additional skill as a kick returner. 
</P>
<P>
Alexander and Anderson were Bay League Co-Players of the Year. 
</P>
<P>
Linebackers Sione Mahe of Hawthorne and Jim Rudberg of Rolling Hills and Palos 
Verdes defensive back Mark Antrobius were named to the defensive unit. Mahe and 
Rudberg were the leading tacklers for their teams, while Antrobius led the 
South Bay with 10 interceptions. 
</P>
<P>
Quarterback Poncho Renteria of division champion Santa Barbara was named 
Division II Player of the Year. 
</P>
