<P>
HIGH SCHOOL SOCCER ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
SAN FERNANDO DRUBS ALEMANY, 4-1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE GLAZE In other tourna 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It was a classic match-up, a battle of undefeated cross-town rivals, Southern 
Section against City, private school meets public. 
</P>
<P>
The contest was surprisingly one-sided, however, as San Fernando High recorded 
a convincing 4-1 win over Alemany in a first-round match of the Hart boys' 
tournament Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Alemany (4-1-1) trailed, 2-0, before trimming the margin toward the end of the 
first half when forward Damon Rivetti, flanked by San Fernando's Tereseso 
Delgado and Ricardo Coyt, flicked the ball into the upper-left corner of the 
net from 12 yards. 
</P>
<P>
San Fernando (5-0-2) took a 3-1 lead 15 minutes into the second half on Enrique 
Moreno's shot from three yards. Two minutes later, Jaime Ballesteros dribbled 
between three Alemany defenders and fired a shot from 10 yards into the left 
side of the net for a 4-1 lead. 
</P>
<P>
In other first-round matches: 
</P>
<P>
Hart 5, Paraclete 1 -- Forward Armando Garcia scored two goals and added an 
assist to lead Hart. 
</P>
<P>
Palmdale 3, Granada Hills 2 -- Striker Arron Cottrell's penalty kick in a 
shoot-out boosted the Falcons (1-1-4) to victory. 
</P>
<P>
Harvard 1, Saugus 0 -- Midfielder Scott Malin scored in the eighth round of 
sudden death to lead the Saracens (7-1-2), who advance to a championship 
quarterfinal match against San Fernando. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 2, Poly 1 -- Forward Prince Board slipped a penalty shot past Poly 
goalkeeper Guillermo Villa in a shoot-out to snap a 1-1 tie. 
</P>
<P>
Camarillo 3, Quartz Hill 1 -- Marcus Hanson scored two goals and Chris Simpson 
added another to lead the Scorpions. 
</P>
<P>
Victor Valley 2, Chatsworth 1 -- Stopper Bill Russell scored the winning goal 
for Victor Valley in a shoot-out. 
</P>
<P>
Newbury Park 3, Hollywood 1 -- A scoreless tie at halftime was broken when 
Panther forward Ryan Keane booted a penalty shot at the five-minute mark. 
Fifteen minutes later, midfielder Mark Stratford scored from five yards for a 
2-0 Newbury Park lead. MIKE GLAZE In other tournaments:ONTARIO CHRISTIAN BOYS 
L. A. Baptist (8-0-2) pitched a pair of shutouts in the first day of play at 
Ontario Christian High, defeating Capistrano Valley Christian, 4-0, and 
Brethren, 12-0. Ron Simpson scored four goals for L. A. Baptist, which will 
play Notre Dame of Riverside in the semifinals Friday at noon.ALTA LOMA GIRLS 
Royal goalkeeper Nikki Noyes chalked up a pair of shutouts to lead the 
Highlanders into the semifinal round. In the first round, Amy Burns and Margi 
