<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CAMARILLO CLAWS BACK TO WIN, 77-71 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAUL OLSON EAGLE ROCK TOURNAMENT Taft 68, Eagle Rock 67 (OT) -- James 
Yoakum's five-foot jum 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Camarillo High won the Ventura tournament in 1983, but getting past the first 
round of late has been a struggle for the Scorpions. 
</P>
<P>
Last year, Camarillo was upset by lowly Oxnard in the first round and Wednesday 
night, in another first-round game at Ventura High, tiny Nordhoff took the 
Scorpions to the limit before succumbing to center Fred Tepesano's three-point 
shots. 
</P>
<P>
Camarillo came from behind to win, 77-71. 
</P>
<P>
Nordhoff (6-4), coming off a tournament championship at Fillmore last week, had 
opened a 60-47 lead heading into the fourth quarter and had thoroughly 
frustrated Camarillo (8-2) until Tepesano found his range. 
</P>
<P>
Tepesano made four three-point shots in the first 4 minutes, 30 seconds of the 
quarter to pull the Scorpions into a 65-65 tie. 
</P>
<P>
The teams traded baskets for the next two minutes before guard David Harbour's 
three-point shot with 2:05 left gave the Scorpions a 72-71 lead they would not 
relinquish. Camarillo kept the Rangers out of the lane down the stretch, 
forcing them to take three-point attempts that would not fall. 
</P>
<P>
Tepesano scored a team-high 25 points and Harbour added 24 points and 10 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
In other first-round games: 
</P>
<P>
Oxnard 63, Channel Islands 59 (3 OTs) -- Guard Rubin Bryant scored four of his 
game-high 16 points in the third overtime period as the Yellowjackets (5-5) 
outscored the Raiders, 7-3, to pull off a mild upset. 
</P>
<P>
Newbury Park 62, Ventura 50 -- Center Kevin Loveall scored 14 points and Tim 
Lane came off the bench to add 14 for Newbury Park (6-3), which will play 
Oxnard in a quarterfinal game at 8 tonight. 
</P>
<P>
Buena 102, Thousand Oaks 91 -- Jeff Oliver scored a game-high 36 points and 
Darren Shearer added 20 to lead the defending tournament-champion Bulldogs 
(5-4). 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks (4-5) was led by forward Chris Loll with 33 points. PAUL 
OLSONEAGLE ROCK TOURNAMENT Taft 68, Eagle Rock 67 (OT) -- James Yoakum's 
five-foot jump shot and free throw with three seconds left in overtime brought 
the Toreadors back from a 19-point third-quarter deficit in a quarterfinal 
game. Yoakum finished with 18 points and sophomore guard Casey Sheahan had 20, 
including a 17-foot jump shot that tied the score, 59-59, with six seconds left 
in regulation. Jason Deyoe scored 16 points and grabbed nine rebounds for Taft 
(9-2), which will play Locke today in the semifinals. Sylmar 91, Garfield 78 
