<DOCNO> LA122889-0044 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 154444 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
December 28, 1989, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Food; Part H; Page 30; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, New Year's Eve Gala -- From left, chefs Daniel Simard, Abdul Eldeib and 
John Grimblot, of Westin South Coast Plaza Hotel in Costa Mesa, put final 
touches on New Year's Eve "Musical Romance" gala dinner. The dinner will 
consist of several appetizers, including lobster brioche, followed by marmite 
of pheasant and pheasant ravioli, roast veal chops with Madeira sauce, 
asparagus tips and carrots with leeks, pasta and, for dessert, a chocolate swan 
filled with raspberry mousse. The event will be held to thank the Pacific 
Symphony Orchestra and the Orange County Philharmonic Society. Los Angeles 
Times 
</P>
