<HEADLINE>
<P>
MONROVIA ALLOWS ITS NEW CHIEF TO REORGANIZE POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MONROVIA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has unanimously approved recommendations by Police Chief 
Joseph Santoro to reorganize the Police Department, which he described as 
"structurally imbalanced." 
</P>
<P>
There are now two divisions in the department: the 60-person operations 
division commanded by a captain and the 15-person support services division 
commanded by a lieutenant. 
</P>
<P>
Santoro, who joined the department in October, suggested shifting the 
investigations bureau from the operations to the support services division and 
making the head of support services a captain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
