<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DISNEY FIRES 3 MEN WHO REFUSED TO SHAVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Walt Disney Attractions, which leases and manages the Queen Mary in Long Beach, 
has fired three mustachioed employees for refusing to abide by company policy 
that bans facial hair. 
</P>
<P>
A Queen Mary spokesman said the union representing the three men has filed 
grievances with Disney, and another union has filed grievances on behalf of 
three employees who shaved their mustaches but were unhappy about having to do 
so. 
</P>
<P>
Although Disney Attractions has been managing the Queen Mary and the nearby 
Spruce Goose for two years, it did not begin enforcing its strict grooming 
policies until this month. 
</P>
