<TEXT>
<P>
Mercantile Exchange to Raise Margins: The New York Mercantile Exchange said it 
is raising its margins on crude, heating oil and unleaded gasoline futures 
contracts. The initial minimum margins on heating oil and unleaded gasoline 
contracts will be raised to $4,000 from $2,000 for customers and to $3,000 from 
$1,600 for clearing members. The margin on crude contracts for customers will 
be raised to $3,000 from $1,250 and to $2,100 from $1,000 for clearing members. 
</P>
