<TEXT>
<P>
Sears Credit Rating Downgraded: Duff &amp; Phelps Inc. said it downgraded its 
credit rating of Sears, Roebuck and Co.'s debt securities because of 
uncertainty over the success of Sears' new retailing strategy. Duff &amp; 
Phelps downgraded Sears' senior debt, acceptance senior debt and Discover Card 
credit senior debt to AA-minus from AA. At the same time, the credit-rating 
company reaffirmed the rating that it gave Sears' commercial paper, Duff 
1-plus. The downgrading affects about $2 billion of debt securities. Duff &amp; 
Phelps said the downgrading reflected the "increased risks and earnings 
volatility" of Sears' retail operations after its switch last spring to a 
strategy of "everyday low pricing." 
</P>
