<HEADLINE>
<P>
EMPLOYEES DONATE $27,000 FOR DISABLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONG BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
McDonnell Douglas West-Personnel Community Service recently donated $27,000 to 
the Long Beach City College Foundation Adaptive Physical Education Associates 
to buy a computerized treadmill for use by disabled students in the Adaptive 
Physical Education program. The funds from McDonnell Douglas West represent 
donations from employees. 
</P>
<P>
Adaptive physical education classes are offered at Long Beach City College to 
give physically handicapped persons an opportunity to strengthen muscles and 
lead a more active life. The associates are seeking additional support to buy 
equipment for the center. For more information, call 420-4267. 
</P>
