Negotiators for striking coal miners and the Pittston Co. resumed talks in 
Washington and were expected to bargain around the clock to settle the 
9-month-long walkout by New Year's Day. The sides returned after a Christmas 
break from negotiations that officials said had come close to agreement. "A 
