<HEADLINE>
<P>
'HOUSE PARTY' TO BOW ON KNBC SCHEDULE JAN. 22 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KNBC-TV Channel 4 will introduce "House Party," an hourlong entertainment and 
information program, to its daily schedule Jan. 22 at 10 a.m. Steve Doocy, a 
former feature reporter for WRC-TV, the NBC-owned station in Washington, will 
host the show that will feature various speciality contributors. 
</P>
<P>
The new series will move into the KNBC-TV lineup in the wake of the 
cancellation of the half-hour daily program, "U.S.A. Today on TV." To make room 
for the one-hour "House Party," Channel 4 will move "Scrabble" to a late-night 
spot, and give new time periods to "Golden Girls" (9 a.m.), "227" (9:30 a.m.) 
and "Classic Concentration" (11 a.m.). 
</P>
<P>
"House Party" is the product of a unique development deal involving Group W, 
the NBC Stations Division, Group W Station Group and NBC Productions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
