<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV RATINGS; 
</P>
<P>
HOLIDAY 'CHEERS' AT NBC; NO. 2 FINISH FOR CBS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVEN LINAN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Cheers" made its way to the No. 1 slot for front-running NBC last week, while 
CBS finished No. 2 for the second week in a row, according to figures released 
Wednesday by the A.C. Nielsen Co. It's the second time this season "Cheers" has 
risen to the top, a position normally taken by ABC's "Roseanne" and NBC's "The 
Cosby Show." In winning the week, NBC's prime-time programs averaged an 
audience of 11.8 million households, compared to 10.8 million for CBS and 10.4 
million for ABC. The full list of ratings is on F12. 
</P>
<P>
* "I Love Lucy Christmas," a nostalgic episode of the classic CBS series that 
had not been shown in 33 years, was the week's sixth-highest-rated program. 
</P>
