<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Oregon lottery's first day of ticket sales for bets tied to NBA games got 
off to what the head of the lottery said was an expected slow start. 
</P>
<P>
Lottery Director Jim Davey said sales were fairly light for the Sports Action 
game, which until now had been limited to professional football bets. 
</P>
<P>
The lottery commission voted to add NBA contests to the game over the league's 
protest. Davey said betting in the sports game picks up as the weekend 
approaches. And he said this week might not be a good one to measure sales 
because substantial numbers of people are off work between the holidays. 
</P>
</TEXT>
