<P>
EX-LT. GOV. HOUSER DIES AT 85 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Frederick F. Houser, California's lieutenant governor under Earl Warren, a 
three-term member of the state Assembly during the 1930s and most recently a 
Los Angeles Superior Court judge, is dead at age 85. 
</P>
<P>
A family member reported today that the veteran Republican lawmaker and jurist 
died Monday at South Coast Medical Center in Laguna Beach after a heart attack. 
</P>
<P>
Houser began his public career at age 25 when he was elected to the Assembly. 
He was chosen Warren's lieutenant governor in 1942 and served one four-year 
term and then was elected to the Superior Court in 1946, retiring 20 years 
later. 
