<TEXT>
<P>
Brown University today acknowledged that Lafayette head Coach Bill Russo turned 
down the top coaching spot at the Ivy League school but would not comment on 
reports that a Nebraska coach had also been offered the post. 
</P>
<P>
"Russo was offered the job and did not accept it," said Brown athletic 
department spokesman Christopher Humm. 
</P>
